# .npmrc.local.example
# Machine-specific npm overrides
#
# npm doesn't support config file concatenation, so machine-specific
# settings (like custom CA certificates) should be set via environment
# variables rather than a separate .npmrc file.
#
# Add to your shell's local config (.bashrc.local, .zshrc.local) or
# project .envrc:
#
#   export NPM_CONFIG_CAFILE=/path/to/corporate-ca-bundle.pem
#   export NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY=https://npm.corp.example.com/
#
# All npm config keys can be set as env vars with the NPM_CONFIG_ prefix.
# See: https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/using-npm/config#environment-variables
